[SN]TITLE[SN]
Overturned lorry causes M8 delays

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A lorry overturned on the M8 in North Lanarkshire, blocking a busy junction and causing long delays.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The incident, involving a lorry and trailer, happened at junction 8 of the motorway near Baillieston roundabout at 13:25.
Police Scotland said the driver of the lorry had suffered a minor arm injury.
The vehicle was later removed and the road reopened just before 21:00. Traffic Scotland had reported lengthy delays.
